caption: Absolutely the best place I've eaten at so far in Chatanooga. The gooey burger is awesome and huge. Coming back to explore the menu. Real burger patties, homemade chips, and homemade pimento cheese. This little deli is a must if you are in Chatanooga. Did I mention friendly service. Sit outback and eat while the kids play in the yard. Just steps away from incline.
Customer service is great, and their blt’s are so good

Worst place I've ever been to food terrible if you eat here you must have covid and can't taste how nasty it is... service was also terrible the guy was a egg plant sucker to us so terrible terrible you have been warmed

By far one of the best burgers my girl and i have ever eaten! I had the gooey burger with sweet potato tots and my girl had the FGT burger with a Greek macaroni salad..absolutely amazing!! If you don't get those burgers they have a great selection of other ones to choose from! Will come back next time we are in Chattanooga!
Good, quick, hand-made sandwiches to go! Been great during Covid crisis. Always felt safe when there

We're from Oak Ridge. We ordered by phone. Friendly service there. Ordered the Reuben with homemade chips and the Hawaiian Ham Wrap with Sweet Potato Tots. The Reuben was just OK. Bread was good. The chips were underwhelming. The Hawaiian Ham Wrap was EXCELLENT! And the Sweet Potato Tots should be trademarked! They're awesome. Also ordered a small serving of the "Real (Wo) Man's Pimento Cheese." The stuff is phenomenal! I arrived early for pick-up and they got it ready right away.  In Anderson County, we're not quite as COVID-phobic as the rest of the world. So, the mask nonsense probably has less to do with St. Elmo Deli & Grill as it does with the city. But it's annoying.
Very Good!
This place is a great spot to get lunch! Definitely get the sweet potato tots if you are into that, you won’t be disappointed!
Excellent food and service.  Would recommend.
Very good sandwiches made with quality ingredients! Takes a while usually and is pretty expensive for a sandwich.
Such a great and tasty local spot. Good service and sandwiches, plus I can walk there.
Friendly service. Good food.
Great food!
Food was good and serves grest
What an amazing sandwich shop! The wrap was delicious and the customer service fantastic!
Awesome food but I always wish they gave you a small pickle with their awesome sandwiches!

Great stop for a bite to eat before going up Lookout Mountain. Wide variety of sandwiches, sides, and all made fresh.  Prices are reasonable for what you get. Plus, during COVID, they have picnic tables so we could eat outside in the back.
The best deli and grill in Saint Elmo!
Great place for a sandwich

We stopped in at St. Elmo Deli and Grill (not to be confused with St. Elmo Grill) after taking a ride on the Incline Railway. We took our sandwiches to go as we needed to get back to the Cleveland area. Our daughter reported her bacon cheeseburger to be good. I had the Caprese Trio and it was good. I would order this again. Their homemade potato chips - so very yummy!
Great deli in St. Elmo needs your support. Drive up and order.
Wonderful food I had a Gooey Burger Best eva
Great, quick sandwich shop. Skip the chips and get one of their better sides.
Delicious made to order sandwiches and burgers
Food is ok. A lil pricey. Not a fan of the hamburger buns they use
Adorable little place with a great menu and friendly staff
Great sandwich & fries!
Tasty joint.  Great pasta salad.  Good service.
Nice staff good food
Try the sweet potato tots!
Great sandwiches
Ok
nice vibe, good food
FGBLT. Get it.
Very good food. I'm from Lubbock,Tx. I will be back to visit you guys in the future. Thank you.
Good food reasonable prices
The food was delicious and the staff members were all very friendly! I recommend the grown-up grilled cheese on sourdough! :)
Great food at a great price. Could not complain about anything.
Food was mediocre, guy taking orders at the front was rude and not helpful, if it was not for the cook coming to talk to me this would only get a 1 star review.
Yummy! Delicious sandwiches made to order.  Right near Incline & Ruby Falls.
Awesome delicious food and great service
Delicious every time! The staff are wonderful as well. I suggest calling ahead if you go here on your lunch break because it can take quite a while sometimes.
Their food is great.
Good food. Had the Italian and it was a little skimpy on meat and flavor. My lunch buddy had the ruben and she said it was ok.
Very good and fast service
Delicious food, comfortable atmosphere, and decent prices. A cute place for a nice lunch. Will definitely be returning.
Awesome sandwich shop. Get the sweet potato tater tots!!! Pay a dollar to park by the incline railway and stop here for lunch.
Tasty sandwiches at a good price. Place was a little grimy.

Fabulous food! My husband and I was looking for something different than a fast food joint. We wanted something like a mom and pops restaurant. We plugged places to eat and St. Elmo Deli & Grill popped up. We contemplated on going in because there was a bus parked in the parking lot and I could see there was a line. But we had nothing but time to kill anyways. Man am I glad we went in. I asked the casher what was good or did they sell the most of. She gave me three offers and I ordered Going Back to Cali with Sweet Potato Tots, oh my how delicious.
The food is always good and the people are very nice
Great food. Friendly,  pleasant staff.
The Buckeye is great!  Not too spicy, just perfect.  House chips are an extra bonus.

Hole in the wall little deli with awesome variety of sandwiches, wraps and salads. Veggie options too. Sweet potato tots were wonderful but chicken salad sandwich left some to be desired. Good lunch after hiking. Great and friendly service.
Great sandwich shop.
The Fried Green Tomato BLT with cajun aioli is genius. I shall return many times just for that.
Food is great

Cute atmosphere, great menu, and decent prices. The young guy working at the front was a little "zoned out" (his own words) but the ladies serving the food were super sweet. Nice place to eat lunch after riding the incline railway.

This place has it all—excellent food, great atmosphere, and super friendly staff. I send all my friends and clients to the Deli because it can’t be beat! My recommendation- get the Gooey Burger and homemade chips. Your life will be changed forever. Peter, the owner, is honest, friendly, and full of hilarious stories. Conveniently located in St. Elmo with plenty of parking and easy access to downtown Chattanooga, Incline Railway, Rock City, or Ruby Falls.

Love love love this place. My favs are the ‘Back to Cali’, smoked Gouda pasta salad, or the ‘Gooey Burger’. The homemade chips are ridiculously good. The owner, Peter, is a great guy and runs a fantastic business. The deli has a fun environment and there is outside seating in the back. We send all of our friends and anyone visiting Chattanooga to this gem in St. Elmo at the foot of Lookout Mtn.
Amazing
Food was excellent.
Ok food

We ordered sandwiches and they were really good. I also liked the chips that came as a side. Finally, the coke and Dr. Pepper out of their fountain was to die for. Don't know if I was extra thirsty, but delish!  Four stars bc the place itself is super duper small, so we felt a little cramped.  Would definitely, at a minimum,  order to go again!
Great food and service. Love the theme of the restaurant and the burgers are exceptional.
Unbelievable amount of flies in the restaurant.
Great wholesome sandwich shop!
Had a burger and fries, very impressed! Great seasonings. Good place to hang out after Ruby Falls and Rock City!
Good, and fresh food with friendly servicd. Chips were home made and fresh. Try to sweet potato fries, they were worth the dollar upcharge.
Nice little restaurant. The salads we're fresh and delicious. The chips are made in house and quite tasty. The bathrooms are small but very clean.
Good stuff
It is a bit expensive but still worth it. The service and the food is great.
Food was good atmosphere not so much and the bathrooms, well... don't ask don't tell...yuck!
For a small indescript deli (drove by it the first time) it was really good food.
Great location, local atmosphere.  Food was served in a timely manner and tasted great!
My only complaint is there are too many delicious options...does that count?
Absolutely delicious!!!

We stopped here after riding the Incline Railway next door. We wanted something quick and tasty, and they didn't disappoint. We had the Cuban and the Reuben. The sandwiches come with home made chips and you can upgrade for a buck. I got the sweet potato tots. All the food was fresh and tasty. The Cuban looked small but is very filling. Would definitely go there again when in the area.
Real persons pimento cheese is yummy!
Awsome food but the homemade chips made me sick.
Fresh food

Great and friendly staff. Highly recommend the fried green tomato BLT. Amazing!!
Not bad for a quick bite.

Our family went here for lunch today. I thought the flavors were pretty good, but the sandwich was small. I had the Porker that literally only had one slice of ham on the sandwich. My son had the kids hotdog and the chips were stale. My wife had the chicken salad salad and the chicken salad was dry.
Great food, owner is friendly. Also locally owned.
Yum, yum, yum! Great sandwiches in a casual setting.
Burger was great. Will be back.
Great burgers!
Freaking awesome spot for a bite to eat. The staff were super cool and friendly.  I got to say if I was living there again it would be my spot. Thanks for the great food guys.
Really good sandwiches and homemade cjips

A small hip deli that specializes in sandwiches. The bulk of their business seems to be serving sandwiches. The menu is written on the wall with specials written on the wall. Food is always quality and fresh. Meat is by Boarshead brand deli meat.
Love the quality of food and service is always on point..thanks guys
Awesome food and great service
Great food!

(Translated by Google) A small restaurant with burgers, sandwiches and salads, which is close to the incline railway and to eat something quick here is fine  (Original) Un restaurante pequeño con hamburguesas , sándwiches y ensaladas , que está cerca del incline railway y para comer algo rápido aquí esta bien
Best Ruebens I have ever had! GREAT FOOD, GREAT PRICES, GREAT SERVICE!!!
Fantastic food!  The going back to cali is simply amazing and the chips are really good. They also have beer.
It's been a favorite spot of mine for the last couple years. The Porker is one of the best sandwiches I've had. Great food here!
Good deli sandwiches & very pleasant staff.

Ate there today. We had the bacon cheddar cheese burger and the hot roast beef sandwich. It was delicious. Came out very fast and hot. Tasted fresh. Servers were very friendly. AWould eat here again. Thank you for fixing our lunch.
Very good food. Hot and fresh. We had bacon cheddar burger and hot roast beef. Was fantastic! Very friendly people.
Everything was fresh and delicious. Go here!
Great sandwiches and a lot of choices.

Restaurant was dirty. Took a long time to get sandwich, which would have been okay if the Cuban would have been hot. Cheese wasn’t even melted. Would have been a good sandwich, otherwise. Greek pasta salad was pretty good. Music was generic elevator style jazz and rather loud, at that. Staff seemed friendly. Will not go back.
Great food.  Fast service.  I'll definitely visit again next time I'm in town.

The food and the service were good and the staff was friendly. My only complaint was that the burgers only include lettuce, tomato, pickle, etc. if you ask for them. That alone isn't much of a problem, but their online menu (which I looked at before going) doesn't make that clear and the person working the counter didn't ask. It is written at the bottom of the in-store menu, but since I already knew what I wanted, I didn't read it until I was on my way out. However, the food seemed good quality and tasted good, so I plan to be back. I would recommend stopping by to grab a bite sometime.
Tried the cubano and the house smoked tenderloin is delicious. The staff is super friendly and service was quick.
Double patty burger and the bun was grilled.  Came out pretty fast and was good.  First time here.  I will stop in again when I'm in the area.  Oh, and very friendly!
Check City hours of operation
Awesome food!  Service was fantastic and super quick!  $$$
The sweet potato tots are awesome.
Fast and friendly.  I had the buckeye and the wife had the smoked chicken salad.  Food was very favorable and arrived quickly. The fries piping hot too.  Would recommend this place.
The sandwiches were a nice change of pace. The homemade chips seemed a little overdone. Helpful people at the counter.

Went here because it was recommended by someone.  Kids grilled cheese was made with something like Kraft processed cheese. Side of fresh fruit....soggy squishy grapes.  Cilantro jalapeno coleslaw had no jalapenos and couldn't taste a hint of cilantro.  Very bland coleslaw.  Plus, had to clean our own table to sit down....not a lot of seating...typical of a deli so that was expected.  The only thing that saved it from one star is the Reuben was alright. Won't be going back.
Favorite place for lunch during work. The chicken salad is a chicken salad... salad, and I'm perfectly fine with that.
Pricey  but  good..
Best food, and great service!
Lunch. Sandwich spot. On point.
Great food good people

So it’s my first time here, my brother recommended this place since it’s not far from my job and great place to meet up and get our grub on. The food is awesome, so flavorful and icing on the cake is the sweet potato tater tots!!! Literally brilliant!!! Should definitely give this little deli a shot, it’s worth it’s price and the employees here are super friendly. To finish off they also support reading, even have a little nook area where you can grab a donated book and just read. Definitely going to come back again in the future 😃
Very good Italian sub

We were looking for something that wasn't a chain restaurant & that's exactly what we found. The house made pimento cheese is what caught my eye. They were really friendly & helpful. I was asking about the ingredients of the jalapeno slaw(for dietary restrictions) he brought out the recipe for me. I ended up getting the "real (wo)man pimento sandwich". Yum
Delicious and fast!
Absolutely delicious!
Wow great food. Blackened chix wrap is awesome. Burgers are seasoned perfect. Fried pickles rock!!!!!! Prices a fair and fast service. Good job

The food was good and fresh and the wait wasn't very long. Great for after exploring lookout mountain.

Nice little place to grab a quick bite.  Staying up the road in Flintstone Georgia.  Reuben was great, and sweet potato tots were hot, so very fresh
Good food quiet place.

An enjoyable, convenient place for lunch before or after riding the Incline Railway. The prices were a little inflated, preparing our order took some time, and my soup was on the sweet side, but otherwise the menu has interesting options, ingredients seemed fresh, staff was friendly, and I'd recommend going.
Great Food.... Great Prices!!!
Awesome food.

Amazing food. Great variety. Even has a little library!
The staff is awesome and ready to serve!  The food is fresh and healthy. The atmosphere is relaxed and inviting. Come by and hang out with friends when you're in town. 😃
Great lunch spot! Good service and a nice variety of menu options. The porker is a great sandwich with a little heat
Awesome food!!! No 1hr wait like the rest of the restaurant...the bread is to die for , you won't regret it.
Best French dip sandwich I've had in a while. The meat is slow roasted on site.
1st time here but I swear to god it won’t be my last.
Good food!
We stopped in during a trip to Ruby Falls. I had the club, it was delicious! The avocado took it to another level. I'd definitely return.

Food was great... Loved the sweet potato tots.

This is by far one of my favorite places. The parking isn’t great and the restaurant isn’t that big, but the food is delicious! I had a veggie sandwich and I could taste the freshness of the ingredients! On a negative note, the employees can be a little more presentable.
Nice employee's, good food.
Bread bought locally fresh

Great deli. They have your traditional sandwiches plus some interesting concoctions and daily specials. The dining area isn't anything special, but it is clean and comfortable. The main attraction is the food!
Avocado burger is great with sweet potato tots!
Great sandwiches .
Great deli ! Got the (Wo)Man's Grilled Pimento Cheese sandwich. It was delicious. Wish I lived closer because I'd probably go everyday.

Food is always cooked with passion. Peter makes a great sandwich, wrap, and sweet potato tots (if that's you're thing, it is mine!). Never had a bad experience and always will go here when I want quality food.

So glad St Elmo has a little deli like this. They use Boar's Head meats and fresh ingredients. The staff is always really nice even when it gets busy for lunch. My favorite is the going back to Cali. And definitely get some of the sweet potato tots, so good!
Good messy burgers!
Great food.  Great service.
Great good at a good price.
Awesome
Excellent!!!!  Everything tasted really great!the Rueben and pimento and cheese was awesome! Drew gives wonderful hugs too!!!
Hamburgers are great and the staff was very friendly was a pleasant meal after a day of family fun.
Sandwiches here are amazing! Limited beer selection but they are all good choices.
Good sandwiches and decent prices.
Excellent place for lunch and has a wonderful atmosphere. It’s a locals place but visitors are welcome! Great place for sandwiches and ice cream.
Recently cited for insects and dirty cooking surfaces.  Bon appetit.
Awesome day on the mountains with 7 kids! Found this great place to eat with our big crowd. Great food, ready to come back next trip!
Good food but a small wrap
Awesome place.  Freshly prepared food, not from a bag or generic food like you'd get somewhere else.
Wonderful food at reasonable price. Close to all the attractions but gives you the chance to support local business and have a breath of fresh air. Will absolutely come back.
Imagine if Jesus Christ made you sandwich. Yeah it's that good....
Not a bad little place to eat. Sandwiches run between 7-10 bucks. They even have PB&J sandwiches!
Great diner! Quaint atmosphere.
Nice little deli with a burger, wrap, sandwich and salad menu. My wife and I had a nice lunch, the turkey Ruben was great. The deli is located right at the entrance to the Incline Railway.
Great food and service
Awesome deli, food, and staff! Love the sweet potato tots!
Truly a great place to eat. I ordered the Back to Cali sandwich with the Greek salad. Very very good. I will go back and recommend to others.
Stopped for a quick bite after a ride on the incline. Great sandwiches and fairly priced. Would definitely recommend. Quick service.
Good food with a beautiful view if you eat out back
Simple. Fresh ingredients. Tasty. Affordable. Friendly staff. Dog-friendly with outdoor seating in back.

Absolutely amazing food that is fresh and flavorful. I love the bread and quality of the homemade pimento cheese. Local companies are so important to our community. You can eat in or take the sandwiches to go for fun up the mountain.  Unfortunately the floors are in poor condition and the paint on the walls are peeling. They have a great kids menu but no baby changing station in the restroom. There is limited free parking in front but plenty of paid parking in back.
The sweet potato tots are INCREDIBLE!!! The sandwich was ok
Can be a bit hectic at lunchtime, but great food in an accessible location.
Second time visiting and as tasty as I remember. House made chips were a little disappointing but a great local spot.
Love the food. I've never been disappointed. Its a nice, cozy atmosphere as well.
Amazing sandwiches! My favorite is the real woman's pimento cheese!
Good food, great service and reasonable prices..  After the long wait on the Incline it was so nice to have a burger, fries and a beer. So glad I stopped there for late lunch
Had the burgers here and they were amazing. The service is great and you feel welcomed immediately. I'll be going back every chance i get. Chattanooga is sleeping on this great little place.

I work in the area and eat here often. Their customer service is out of this world. They use local bread and boar's head meat, and make amazing sweet potato tots. I hear the smoked chicken salad is out of this world, but i just can't get away from the Reuben. Goin Back to Cali, and the pimento cheese sandwiches are great.
Indrecible! Everything here is delicious from the unique sandwiches to the sides. The Going back to Cali is to die for!
I love the smoked chicken salad sandwich with house made potato chips.

When in on a Saturday at 3:30. Only two people eating in the place. Not a clean table To be found. Not just cluttered but food and garbage on every table. Almost left without eating. Glad we stayed. The food was really good but it will be a while before I go back due to the filth.
Good pricing and quality. Been going here for years. Accurate on to-go orders. Very fast.
Amazing food , great prices , and a relaxing atmosphere.
Great little relaxed deli with delicious sandwiches made with Boar's Head meats. Our family enjoys it, and our office likes to get take out from there.
I had the Fried Green Burger with bacon and Cajun Aioli sauce and a side of sweet potatoe tots . Awesome!!!!
My family go to place in St Elmo delicious food and great service
Excellent
Best food in Chattanooga. Hands down!
Excellent sandwiches. Homemade chips are incredible! Had the Italian Job. Fresh meat. Bread was delicious as well.
quaint little nook at the bottom of the incline railway.  good food.  deli style delicious.  get the pickle.  the 3yr old devoured it, turning down fries.  i got the blt fried green tomato... mmmmmm
Great sandwiches and the owners are fantastic
